task.summary: Add services and controllers from previous course and include it in Ionic application. Start design home page.
Design menu page and dish detail page

Assignment 1. Update the Contact Us page to show the address and the three buttons like a button-bar with ionic icon. Update the About Us page to show the history and list of corporate leaders of the restaurant.
Ionic Modals and Forms. Create form for reservation table.
Ionic item list . Create custom filter. Create favorite dishes page and interface to control this list
Use popups for delete item from favorites. Show loading when favorite page don't loading yet.
Assignment 2. Create popover in dishdetail page with 2 options: Add in Favorite and Add Comment. Create form for add comment and apply data to the server.
Use resolve within the ui-router state to support a map of dependencies, and provide data to the controller
Use $rootscope events ($stateChangeSuccess and $stateChangeStart) to trigger the showing and hiding of a loading message

Update the home, menu and aboutus states in app.js to use resolve to support data resolution in the ui-router Make use of local storage support in the app to persist the user's favorite dishes on the device.
Use Cordova plugin for splash screen

Delivering notification to the user. Use the local notification plugin to put a notification into the device's notification bar. Use the toast plugin to show a short message on the screen to alert the user.
Use Cordova camera plugin in order to get photo from the camera on register page.
